{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ed76faa9-449f-4687-aa0f-3fd4a22b8769","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n\n| Target | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped — EOL, not supported by MSTest v3 |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped — EOL, not supported by MSTest v3 |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for .NET (Core) targets. You'll need to update `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` to at least `net6.0` (or ideally `net8.0`, since .NET 6 is also EOL).\n\n**Other migration notes:**\n- MSTest v3 offers a single **`MSTest`** meta-package, replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n- Some APIs were removed or had breaking behavioral changes (e.g., stricter assertions, `DataRow` attribute changes). Review your tests after upgrading.\n\n**Suggested updated `.csproj`:**\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n...\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.7.3\" />\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9272e556-ea99-4783-b233-be4bfc23e35c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate to MSTest v3. Let me analyze the compatibility issues.\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n- MSTest v3 requires .NET 6.0+ for .NET (Core) targets, so `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` are no longer supported.\n- For .NET Framework, MSTest v3 requires .NET Framework 4.6.2+, so `net462` should be fine.\n\nWait, let me be more precise. \n\nSo the user will definitely have compatibility issues with `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` targets since both are end-of-life and no longer supported by MSTest v3. They'd need to update those to at least `net6.0`, or ideally `net8.0` for better long-term support.\n\nMSTest v3 also simplified the package structure—there's now a single `MSTest` meta-package that bundles everything together, though the individual `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages are still available if needed.","outputTokens":722,"requestId":"E3C6:182BD0:1CDBB9E:205C8CC:6A053BDA"},"id":"af7ce0d3-0323-45a3-8bbc-1f2009609c4f","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:05:13.061Z","parentId":"f0981318-eb7b-4512-a86b-801e2a8644ca"}
